    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a pinnacle of analog engineering. This specimen features the M96 3.6L flat-six powerplant, delivering a linear 320hp through a precision-gated six-speed manual transaxle. The mechanical profile is impeccable: the IMS bearing and Rear Main Seal (RMS) have been proactively addressed with LN Engineering components, and a recent bore-scope confirms pristine cylinder walls. The suspension geometry remains factory-tight, utilizing its original MacPherson strut and multi-link configuration for razor-sharp turn-in. Zero fluid seepage, flawless underbody aerodynamics, and a localized paint depth consistency confirm its survivor status. This is a turn-key enthusiast acquisition with optimal compression across all cylinders.",
      "price": 48500.0,
